===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
In the Warring States period, the character existed in the forms {{zh-l|*𢿑}} and {{zh-l|*𱡡}}; the latter of which is likely the ancestor of the modern form, a {{Han compound|ls=psc|米|攴|禼|c3=p|t1=rice|t2=action}} – theft.

In the western Han the component {{zh-l|*宀|building}} was added to emphasize the meaning of theft. The component {{och-l|禼}} would often be written as {{och-l|萬}} due to their graphic and phonetic similarity.

In eastern Han seal script, {{zh-l|*宀}} had corrupted into {{zh-l|*穴}}. This form also included a {{och-l|*廿}} subcomponent, which is likely a corruption of the upper part of {{och-l|*萬}}, while the lower part corrupted back into the original phonetic component {{och-l|禼}}. ''{{w|Shuowen}}'' regards {{och-l|*廿}} as the phonetic component, although that is not etymologically accurate. 

In the modern form, {{zh-l|*米}} has corrupted into {{zh-l|*釆}}, and the {{och-l|*廿}} from seal script is omitted.

